    "body": "### Problem\n\n> reproduce steps might be more understandable\r\n\r\nI was going to get a full gutter width by `vim.fn.getwininfo(win)[1].textoff`.\r\n\r\nBut even if I set `number signcolumn=yes`, the value of `textoff right after the `:vsplit` is `4` and not `6`.\r\n\r\nI can see it is 6 because of signcolumn width and when I manually retrieve the `textoff` value from command line, it says it is `6`.\r\nBut neovim says it is `4` right after the `WinEnter` event.\r\n\r\n> [!NOTE]\r\n> this doesn't happen from vim\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n**repro.lua**:\r\n```lua\r\n-- to show 'number' option is working\r\nvim.o.number = true\r\nvim.o.signcolumn = \"yes\"\r\nvim.cmd.wincmd(\"v\")\r\nlocal infos = vim.fn.getwininfo()\r\n-- new window\r\nvim.print(infos[1].winid, infos[1].textoff)\r\n-- original window\r\nvim.print(infos[2].winid, infos[2].textoff)\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean -u repro.lua`\r\n2. the output is like this:\r\n    ```\r\n    1001\r\n    4\r\n    1000\r\n    6\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n> This doesn't happen from vim. Tested with this script:\r\n> **repro.vim**\r\n> ```vim\r\n> set number\r\n> set signcolumn=yes\r\n> \r\n> wincmd v\r\n> \r\n> let infos = getwininfo()\r\n> echom infos[0].textoff\r\n> echom infos[1].textoff\r\n> ```\r\n> Running `vim -u repro.vim` prints:\r\n> ```\r\n> 10\r\n> 10\r\n> ```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTwo windows should have same `textoff` value right after the split.\r\nSo output should be like this:\r\n```\r\n1001\r\n6\r\n1000\r\n6\r\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 8.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nblink shell\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256-color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
